@startuml redundant_physical_connection_virtual_servers
!include ../../../../../../tooling/styles/plantuml/behavioral/activity-diagram-style.iuml

title Redundant Physical Connection for Virtual Servers Architecture\nStandby uplink takes over transparently when the primary uplink fails

start
:Add second NIC to host (1);
:Connect both NICs to physical switch (2);
:Configure both NICs as virtual switch uplinks (3);
:Designate primary uplink (4);
:Designate secondary uplink as standby
(receives packets but does not forward);

repeat
  :Virtual servers send traffic
  via primary uplink;
  if (Primary uplink available?) then (yes)
    :Secondary remains in standby
    (no forwarding);
  else (no  (5))
    :Failover system promotes
    standby to active uplink (6);
    :Secondary uplink forwards
    virtual server packets externally;
    :Virtual servers remain
    connected (transparent) (7);
    if (Failed uplink returns to operation?) then (yes)
      :Failed uplink resumes as primary;
      :Other NIC returns to standby;
    else (no)
      :Continue on secondary uplink;
    endif
  endif
repeat while (host running?) is (yes)
->no;
stop

note right
  Supporting mechanisms:
  Failover System (transition to standby),
  Hypervisor, Logical Network Perimeter
  (per-consumer virtual switch isolation),
  Resource Replication (replicate active
  uplink status to standby).
end note

@enduml
